commentTextItems.html: turns into him, misses it by a mile, gets struck on the pad, an appeal turned down

commentPostTextItems.html: Well folks, Afghanistan have claimed the first match by 12 runs (D/L). Zimbabwe were ahead by a one run before Burl was timely trapped in  front by Rashid Khan to give the fielding team advantage then the heavens opened up and with that all the chances of Zimbabwe recovering went up in smoke. The groundstaff did their best but it wasn't enough to save the home side.
17:05 Match called off , Afghanistan won by 12 runs
Umpires are having a chat with both the captains
All four umpires, the match referee, are on field now
A small roller is being pulled over the outfield, and some sawdust is being sprinkled on the area
The scores is likely to be revised again after this delay Umpires are walking off the field.
there seems to be a bit of a problem. The Afghanistan players aren't happy about something , probably the outfield
the two batsmen are walking back to the pavilion after having a chat with the umpires
now the Afghanistan fielders are marching out of the field
groundsmen are back back on field. There seems to be a problem area just outside the square.
and we are back.. the two umpires walks out into the field. being followed by the Afghan team and the two batsmen takes to the field
Afghanistan are ahead by 13 runs on DL
and its raining now .. the Players are running off the field....... the smaller covers are being pulled on to the wicket
and now the bigger cover is now being pulled over the table
Some good news.... it has stopped raining..... covers are being pulled off
Though its still heavily overcast
46 overs to be played, target revised to 207 and starts at 16:30 local

commentTextItems.html: full, on middle and leg, drives towards mid off
leans back, slaps it wide of mid off, who dives but to no reward, rolls down to the boundary. Well struck

dismissalText.commentary: Noor Ali Zadran lbw b Cremer 39 (71b 4x4 0x6 112m) SR: 54.92

dismissalComment.html: Cremer strikes again!!.. bowled it bit quicker through the air, on off and middle, turns back sharply, Zadran gets behind his pads and got trapped in front on his sticks! third one bits the dust for 97

dismissalText.commentary: Hashmatullah Shahidi run out (Mpofu) 21 (44b 1x4 0x6 55m) SR: 47.72

dismissalComment.html: Gone!!! pitched outside off, Asghar drives it tamely, sets off for a single, Mpofu charges down from his follow through, fielded and hits direct at the strikers stumps, Shaidi is well short

dismissalText.commentary: Asghar Afghan c Musakanda b Sikandar Raza 50 (57b 1x4 2x6 76m) SR: 87.71

dismissalComment.html: gone! comes down the track, whacks it in the air, had no power to clear the boundary, Musakanda lurking at cow corner settles under it and pouches

headshotImage.caption: Chris Mpofu player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Chris Mpofu player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Nabi c Mire b Mpofu 6 (12b 0x4 0x6 13m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: gone! and Nabi departs, poor shot that! length ball, on middle and leg, Nabi comes down the track, whacks it high in the Harare skies, Mire charges from long on, settles well under it, collects it in front of his face

dismissalText.commentary: Gulbadin Naib c & b Cremer 1 (3b 0x4 0x6 4m) SR: 33.33

dismissalComment.html: 7 down! poor poor shot!, tossed up, on middle and leg, turning away, Naib tries to glance it, gets a leading edge straight to Cremer who takes an easy chest height catch

dismissalText.commentary: Najibullah Zadran c Burl b Mpofu 11 (18b 0x4 0x6 30m) SR: 61.11

dismissalComment.html: Gone. Well taken!, length ball, outside off, Zadran clears his front leg, punches it in the air towards Burl fielding at deep point who runs in dives forward and takes a low catch

dismissalText.commentary: Dawlat Zadran c Moor b Chatara 2 (6b 0x4 0x6 6m) SR: 33.33

dismissalComment.html: taken! outside off, hold its line, stays bit low,  Zadran played for bounce, gets a thick outside edge through to Moor, who dives forward and takes the catch

dismissalText.commentary: Rashid Khan c Sikandar Raza b Chatara 32 (18b 3x4 2x6 31m) SR: 177.77

dismissalComment.html: all over! Afghanistan bowled out for 215!, on a length, outside off, Rashid Khan clears his front foot, hits it in the air to the leg side, Raza sprints from the boundary at long on, settles under it, waits and takes the catch

dismissalText.long: c Dawlat Zadran b Mohammad Nabi
dismissalText.commentary: Peter Moor c Dawlat Zadran b Mohammad Nabi 18 (20b 4x4 0x6 21m) SR: 90

dismissalComment.html: GONE!, regarded as one of the best spin players in the country and he is done by Nabi, tossed up, on middle and leg, Moor tonks it high but not far towards Dawlat Zadran who back paddles and takes the simple catch

dismissalText.commentary: Solomon Mire lbw b Amir Hamza 2 (11b 0x4 0x6 15m) SR: 18.18

dismissalComment.html: GONE!!!, full on off stump, turns back, Mire tires to work it away but is struck on the front pad, first one bits the dust.

dismissalText.commentary: Craig Ervine not out 38 (56b 2x4 0x6 99m) SR: 67.85

dismissalText.long: c Mohammad Nabi b Gulbadin Naib
dismissalText.commentary: Sikandar Raza c Mohammad Nabi b Gulbadin Naib 12 (30b 2x4 0x6 35m) SR: 40

dismissalComment.html: GOEN! back of a length, outside off, Raza tries forcing it to the leg side again, hits it tamely in the air to mid on who takes a simple catch

milestones.description: Afghanistan's 116-run win against Zimbabwe is the largest margin of victory in terms of runs in ODIs, beating 100-run win against Zimbabwe
Dawlat Zadran has broken the record for most ducks (5) in ODIs for AFG, going past Asghar Afghan's 5

stories.title: Afghanistan win on D/L after Burl falls just before rain
stories.subTitle: Zimbabwe v Afghanistan, 1st ODI, Harare
stories.seoTitle: Afghanistan win on D/L after Ryan Burl falls just before rain
stories.summary: Afghanistan completed a 12-run win via Duckworth-Lewis calculations after the rain arrived in Harare with Zimbabwe on 99 for 4, chasing 216
